Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: ModSecurity not blocking attacks

Verify SecRuleEngine On in modsecurity.conf
Check that ModSecurity module is loaded: nginx -V 2>&1 | grep modsecurity
Review audit log for rule matches: sudo tail -f /var/log/modsec/audit.log
Issue: Nginx fails to start after ModSecurity configuration

Test configuration: sudo nginx -t
Check for syntax errors in rule files
Verify file permissions: ls -la /etc/nginx/modsec/
Review error log: sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log
Issue: Backend application not accessible

Verify backend is running: sudo systemctl status webapp
Check if port 8080 is listening: sudo netstat -tlnp | grep 8080
Test direct backend access: curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/
Issue: Python script permission errors

Run with sudo for system file access
Check file ownership: ls -la /etc/nginx/modsec/
Verify log file permissions: ls -la /var/log/modsec/
